5, [1] p.
printed by John Bill and Christopher Barker, printers to the Kings most excellent Majesty, [London : 1664]
Title from caption title (p. 3). Imprint from title page, which reads: Anno regni Caroli II. Regis Angliæ, Scotiæ, Franciæ, & Hiberniæ, decimo sexto. At the Parliament begun at Westminster the eighth day of May, anno Dom. 1661. .. At head of p. 3: Anno XVI. Caroli II. Regis. Text in black letter. On A1r, last word of first line of text: made; first word of line below initial: blessed; last word of last full line of text: the. Signatures: pi¹ A1 B1. Reproduction of the original in the Harvard University Library.
